	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The whole thing would be 113 cycles if you want a beam going one pixel back, or 114 cycles if you want a beam going two pixels further per scanline. </div>
<br />
<br />Actually, 113 cycles would go 2 pixels back and 114 cycles would go 1 pixel forward. Remember, the NES CPU executes 113+<strong>2</strong>/3 cycles (341 / 3) per scanline.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


